"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"**Problem Statement**: You’ve got a list of some sort that you would like to filter using a drop down menu on your web page. How do you do this using vanilla javascript? \\n\\n**Inspiration**: This is a problem that took me way too long to solve via Googling. Here is a working solution for those of you that find yourselves in a similar situation. \\n\\n### Example\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/NnYzFFHvKV8O6S3UnVFyl.png?height=512&width=350)\\n\\nSay you’ve got the following <li> elements above and you want to dynamically filter them based on the <option> selected in your <select> element. Here are the steps required in building that functionality: \\n\\n* Give your <select> element an id so you can reference it in your javascript file. \\n* Once you’ve referenced the <select> element, add a \\\"change” Event Listener to it. \\n* Pass the event object into the call back function. \\n* Reference the value of the selection by setting a variable equal to e.target.value. \\n* Reference the unchanged list by setting a variable equal to document.querySelectorAll(‘li’).\\n* Within the body of the call back function, write a for loop that iterates over each item in the unchanged list and sets the style.display attribute of that item to nothing (item.display.attribute = ‘‘). This is so that successive filters do not whittle down the original list.\\n* Within the body of the callback function, write a for loop that iterates over the list of elements and compares the first letter of the list element to selection made by the user (which we referenced using e.target.value). \\n* Within the body of your for loop, write an if statement that sets the style.display attribute of that item to ‘none’ if the first letter off the list element does not match the selection made by the user. \\n\\n### Code\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/VMN370tSbOyuU8K-O58Fu.png?height=385&width=419)\\n\\nI hope this saved you some Googling. \",\"timestamp\":1637614764,\"title\":\"Dynamically Filtering a List Using Vanilla Javascript\"},\"digest\":\"k_0ot5x0PesZQX21CEVAhk2_2Ug3cW19HofA49OB4E4\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xdD0868dAF82E38808130eCdbD998013a654637Ae\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"y7a2poFmn3SDJ7u_42nimdO71R3sj9Hj6TKUVHufMUM\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"Bh5TgTmlEcqiIeKcVPsQNS-wI_xQyTVtJ9HueorWlnY\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"U6BSABseWj0AQH-ZEFDHEQQaxVLRyC_HiEwef1FS7V8dlahMRkgHxT3MS5YMri_xTAboOFX0Xutjj8AlYOvrQw\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x0cc14121df563289af491316180fb4068c2008995ec3228ccd90432053a50fe2622a31aaf80232ad7a7c73ccb8d6def4fb50551791e0e34058bb51ec532bd93c1b\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"y7a2poFmn3SDJ7u_42nimdO71R3sj9Hj6TKUVHufMUM\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"Bh5TgTmlEcqiIeKcVPsQNS-wI_xQyTVtJ9HueorWlnY\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"k_0ot5x0PesZQX21CEVAhk2_2Ug3cW19HofA49OB4E4\"}"